    "Table 11 shows the results of the few-shot experiments.",
    "In the AI-generated review detection experiments, the proposed method still performed well with only 32 training samples, obtaining an average F1 measure of 0.8732.",
    "This finding shows that the proposed method still has good stability when a small number of samples is used and provides strong support for the actual application scenario of data scarcity.",
    "According to the experimental results of the attribute-grained preference analysis, when the training set consists of 32 and 128 samples, the performance of the model is acceptable.",
    "As the number of training samples increases to 256, the F1 measure of the model significantly increases to 0.8125."
